<item>
            <title>[SOLR-16433] Security Manager prevents Solr SQL from working</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16433</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Workaround: set SOLR_SECURITY_MANAGER_ENABLED=false. This is only defaulted to true in Solr 9.0. Previously with Solr 8.x this was set to false.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was reported on the Solr user list:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://lists.apache.org/thread/hbozfyn9xpno2tk573pk3vjbyhohyqnm&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://lists.apache.org/thread/hbozfyn9xpno2tk573pk3vjbyhohyqnm&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Calcite tries to initialize and check a few paths for the test dataset, but the security manager throws an exception for this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/calcite/blob/main/core/src/main/java/org/apache/calcite/config/CalciteSystemProperty.java#L189&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/calcite/blob/main/core/src/main/java/org/apache/calcite/config/CalciteSystemProperty.java#L189&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m tracking this down in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CALCITE-5298&quot; title=&quot;CalciteSystemProperty calcite.test.dataset path check fails under Java Security Manager&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CALCITE-5298&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CALCITE-5298&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13049732/13049732_Calcite+Exception.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
