                            <comment id="17609207" author="mdrob" created="Sun, 25 Sep 2022 15:17:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I suspect this is only an issue on Java 11?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17609216" author="risdenk" created="Sun, 25 Sep 2022 15:47:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mdrob&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mdrob&quot;&gt;mdrob&lt;/a&gt; - I don&apos;t think this is specific to Java 11. The default for security manager changed from false -&amp;gt; true in Solr 9. It looks like this would have been a problem in JDK 8 with Solr 8 with security manager enabled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I opened PR &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/solr/pull/1044&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/solr/pull/1044&lt;/a&gt; which should workaround &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CALCITE-5298&quot; title=&quot;CalciteSystemProperty calcite.test.dataset path check fails under Java Security Manager&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CALCITE-5298&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CALCITE-5298&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in the meantime.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17609237" author="mdrob" created="Sun, 25 Sep 2022 18:54:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I meant it wouldn&#8217;t be a problem with Java 17 when security manager has been significantly defanged&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17615811" author="risdenk" created="Tue, 11 Oct 2022 13:34:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah yea that might be true. From what I understood - in JDK 17 security manager was just deprecated and warnings added. I don&apos;t think any actual functionality was removed. &lt;a href=&quot;https://seanjmullan.org/blog/2021/09/14/jdk17#security-manager&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://seanjmullan.org/blog/2021/09/14/jdk17#security-manager&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
